* Zyber raises her head a bit, and tries to rais herself to her feet but it 
was useless.
She almost seemed to quiver as DeathScythe walked up to her, knowing that 
this was probably her final hour. She really didn't want to die, but she 
couldn't move no matter how she tried.
Zyber closed her optics, at least she wouldn't see him pull the trigger.

She was about ready to hear the click of the trigger when she suddenly head 
DeathScythe laugh, and him speak words she least expected.
He was going to let her live?
Had he seen the true light after all, that killing other bots just because 
he thought they were weak?

Zyber grunted as DeathScythe kicked her, actually doubling over and curling 
around here stomach where his foot contacted with.
She guessed not!
She opens her optics a bit to see him turn and walk off, simply laying there 
and trying to stand the pain.*
